               <head>Extracts on Afghanistan</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary/>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85064939 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85001521"
                     n="1" xml:id="Uk_IO_Islamic_3765-item1">
                     <note>
                        <p>Miscellaneous extracts and tracts in Persian relating to the history of
                           Afghanistan with an informal title: <title>Kitāb-i naṣab nāmah-'i
                              khavānīn-i Durrānī va ʿunvānī va Fārsī zabān-i sākinīn-i Qandahār va
                              Kābul</title>
                        </p>
                        <p>Some variation in dimensions of individual tracts. </p>
                        <p>According to a colophon (f. 165v): completed at the request of Captain
                           William Anderson Ṣāḥib Bahādur in dār al-salṭanah Qandahār, Tuesday 19
                           Jum. I 1258/28 June 1842, by Mīrzā Yaḥyá the munshīʾ </p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="eng">Persian &amp; English</textLang>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
               <physDesc>
                  <objectDesc form="codex">
                     <supportDesc material="chart">
                        <extent>ff. 166<dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
                              <height>210</height>
                              <width>175</width>
                           </dimensions>
                           <dimensions type="written" unit="mm"/>
                        </extent>
                     </supportDesc>
                  </objectDesc>
                  <handDesc>
                     <handNote script="Arabic" scope="major">
                        <p>Cursive nastaʻlīq; copied in black ink. Copied by <persName role="scr"
                           key="person_f8601">Mīrzā Yaḥyā Munshī</persName>. </p>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <p>Annotations in English. </p>
                     <p>Signed note on f. 166v by <persName>William Anderson (1803-1858)</persName>
                        dated August 1842: "This book contains a few memoirs of some of the leading
                        men about Kundahar and Kabul, such as generally received; collected by Mirza
                        Yahya...many are common tradition and may not be true." </p>
                  </additions>
                  <bindingDesc>
                     <binding when="1842">
                        <decoNote>Contemporary brown leather binding with plain and punched circle
                           borders. </decoNote>
                     </binding>
                  </bindingDesc>
